abstract: A battle over gun regulations in New Hampshire took a strange turn this week: Lawmakers wore pearls, and gun control advocates said they were being mocked.
snippet: A battle over gun regulations in New Hampshire took a strange turn this week: Lawmakers wore pearls, and gun control advocates said they were being mocked.
lead_paragraph: People on opposite sides of the debate about guns apparently can’t agree on anything these days — not even the meaning of a string of pearls.

abstract: The billionaire former New York City mayor said he would not seek the presidency, avoiding a crowded primary field that is generally to the left of him.
snippet: The billionaire former New York City mayor said he would not seek the presidency, avoiding a crowded primary field that is generally to the left of him.
lead_paragraph: Michael R. Bloomberg, the former New York City mayor who joined the Democratic Party last year to crusade against President Trump, announced he would not seek the White House himself in 2020, discarding plans to mount a maverick campaign that would have tested the party’s openness to a wealthy centrist with a chameleon-like approach to partisan politics.

abstract: Initially criticized for his ties to the pharmaceutical industry, Gottlieb, a former venture capitalist, became known for his aggressive regulatory stance in the Trump administration.
snippet: Initially criticized for his ties to the pharmaceutical industry, Gottlieb, a former venture capitalist, became known for his aggressive regulatory stance in the Trump administration.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Scott Gottlieb, the commissioner of the Food and Drug Administration, known for his aggressive efforts to regulate the tobacco and e-cigarette industries, said on Tuesday that he would resign at the end of the month.
